      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial legal doctrine that protects fundamental rights from government overreach, ensuring that the government cannot infringe upon deeply rooted liberties. It has been instrumental in expanding civil rights by striking down laws that infringe upon personal autonomy, such as those related to privacy and bodily integrity. This concept affirms that certain rights are so fundamental they cannot be taken away, regardless of how the legislature frames the law. It is a vital bulwark against tyranny and government intrusion into private life.",
